\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2. God wanted to show\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 forever picture\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 that the sacrifice He wants is a spiritual and living sacrifice. God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s concern is the spiritual sacrifice of man\u8217\'92s body, not a human sacrifice. God wants man to offer his body as a living sacrifice. God does not want people offering their children and beautiful women to God by laying them upon altars and killing them. God wants people offering themselves and their children and beautiful women as living sacrifices to Him.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I beseech you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God, that ye present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable unto God, which is your reasonable service\u8221\'94 (Ro. 12:1)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 3. God wanted to show\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 forever picture\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the sacrifice of Christ at Calvary, the sacrifice of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s very own Son for the sins of the world. There are many similarities between the offering of Abraham\u8217\'92s son, Isaac, and the offering of God\u8217\'92s Son, the Lord Jesus Christ. The similarities will be covered below. (See note, pt. 3, Thought 1\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 22:11\endash 14 for discussion.)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 4. God wanted to show\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 forever picture\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 that He does test people; He tests them to show the world that some persons do fear God. By }{\f0\fs24\i1 fear}{\f0\fs24  is meant reverence, love, awe, and true worship\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 all that true religion is. This was the very reason God gave for testing Abraham: verse one says that God tested Abraham and verse twelve tells why God tested him, to show that Abraham feared (reverenced, loved) God above all else, even above his very own son. This fact is discussed in more detail below (see note\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 22:1\endash 2 for more discussion).}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {\f0\fs24  This is the subject of this great passage: }{\f0\fs24\i1 Abraham Sacrificed Isaac: Supreme, Sacrificial Faith\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the Steps to Absolute Surrender}{\f0\fs24 , 22:1\endash 24.}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1.\tab Step 1: facing God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s demand for absolute sacrifice, His highest demand (vv. 1\endash 2).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2.\tab Step 2: thinking through the sacrifice (vv. 3\endash 4).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 3.\tab Step 3: trusting God and His power to raise up and use the sacrifice (vv. 5\endash 8).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 4.\tab Step 4: following through with the sacrifice (vv. 9\endash 10).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 5.\tab Step 5: experiencing God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s acceptance and provision (vv. 11\endash 14).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 6.\tab Step 6: having God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises renewed to one\u8217\'92s heart (vv. 15\endash 18).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 7.\tab Conclusion: receiving good news (vv. 19\endash 24).}
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (Please note: a person may wish to divide this passage into two or three messages or lessons. If so, the following is suggested:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Part 1 could cover just point 1 of the outline, vv. 1\endash 2.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Part 2 could cover points 2\endash 4 of the outline, vv. 3\endash 10.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Part 3 could cover points 5\endash 6, vv. 11\endash 24.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Of course, other divisions are possible, as well as the teaching of the passage as a whole. May our wonderful Lord help us share with power the great truths pictured so graphically in this most startling passage.)\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge22.1-24&off=7003&ctx=+sacrifice+for+man.%0a~2.+God+wanted+to+sho"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 133). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 1}{\f0\fs24  (22:1\endash 2) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Testing\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Surrender\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Dedication\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Sacrifice\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Religions, False\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Human Sacrifice}{\f0\fs24 : step one to absolute surrender is facing God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s demand for absolute sacrifice, His supreme highest demand.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 a. God tested Abraham, put him in a severe crisis. Remember, this was not the only major test or crisis Abraham had to face (see }{\f3\fs20\scaps Deeper Study}{\f3\fs20  # 1}{\f0\fs24 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 22:1\endash 2 for more discussion). J. Vernon McGee says this:}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\i1 This is a real crisis in Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s life. God has brought this man through four very definite crises, each of which was a real exercise of his soul, a real strain upon his heart}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 First of all, he was called to leave all of his relatives in Ur of the Chaldees. He was just to leave the whole group. That was a real test for Abraham. He didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t do it very well at the beginning, but, nevertheless, the break finally came}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 Then there was the test that came with Lot, his nephew. Abraham loved Lot\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 he wouldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t have been carrying Lot around with him if he hadn\u8217\'92t. But the time came when they had to separate, and Lot went down to Sodom}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 Then there was the test with this boy of his, the son of Hagar, Ishmael. Abraham just cried out to God, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, that Ishmael might live before Thee!\u8221\'94 He loved that boy; he hated to be separated from him}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 Now Abraham comes to this supreme test, the fourth great crisis in his life: he is asked to give up Isaac. Abraham does not quite understand all the details for the very simple reason that God has told him, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91In Isaac your seed shall be called.\u8217\'92 Abraham believed God would raise Isaac from the dead (see He. 11:19), but as far as Abraham is concerned, he is willing to go through with the sacrifice}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 b. God asked Abraham to do a most difficult thing: to offer his son as a sacrifice to God, the son whom he loved ever so dearly. Note how God stressed Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s love for his son: take your son, }{\f0\fs24\i1 whom you love}{\f0\fs24 , and offer him as a sacrifice. Abraham was given Isaac in his old age (Ge. 21:2, 5). He had been hoping for the promised son for decades, and he had all his dreams wrapped up in him. Why would God demand such a thing from Abraham?}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Very simply, God was putting Abraham to the supreme test of life, the absolute sacrifice and surrender of himself to God. Step by step God led him to the point of absolute surrender. How?}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1)\tab God led Abraham to absolute surrender by taking the most precious thing in his life and leading him to surrender that thing as an offering, as a sacrifice to God. It was Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart, his willingness, his spiritual surrender that God was after, not Isaac\u8217\'92s life. (See the passages forbidding human sacrifice\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Le. 18:21; 20:1\endash 5; De. 12:31; 18:10.)}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2)\tab God led Abraham to absolute surrender by testing him within his environment. God always has to use the language and the things of a man\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s environment if He wishes His message to be communicated and understood. In Abraham\u8217\'92s day the sacrifice of human beings was the supreme act of worship by some heathen religions, for example Canaanite religions. A worshipper who offered his own flesh and blood was thought to be offering the supreme sacrifice. He was proving that he loved his god supremely, above all else.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 When God told Abraham to sacrifice Isaac, Abraham knew exactly what God was saying to him. He was to make the supreme sacrifice, prove that he loved the only true and living God above all else. Abraham knew that God was after the absolute surrender of his heart, his will, his spirit. Verse five compared with He. 11:19 shows this (see note below\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 22:5\endash 8).}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . God did not test Abraham that Abraham might prove himself to God. God knew Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart. God knows all things. But Abraham needed to know his own heart, and all future believers needed a picture of what absolute surrender to God means, a testimony that man can love God supremely. Man can make an absolute surrender and sacrifice of himself to God (all he is and has), and God can take care of him, no matter what may confront him. Thus the testing of Abraham took place in order }{\f0\fs24\i1 to show}{\f0\fs24  and teach several things to both Abraham and succeeding generations.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (1)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can know God personally. A person can actually have a personal relationship with God. This is shown by the name used for God (Ha \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91Elohim) (v. 1). The Hebrew name here stresses the personal, true God. It was the personal, true God (Ha \u8216\'91Elohim) who spoke to Abraham, not just God (Elohim, the general name used for God).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Behold, I stand at the door, and knock: if any man hear my voice, and open the door, I will come in to him, and will sup [fellowship] with him, and he with me\u8221\'94 (Re. 3:20)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But as many as received him, to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name\u8221\'94 (Jn. 1:12)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (2)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can love God supremely. A person can love God before all else, even before his son or daughter (Ge. 22:2, 10). (See outline and notes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Mt. 10:35\endash 37 for more information.)}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me: and he that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me\u8221\'94 (Mt. 10:37)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Jesus said unto him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind\u8221\'94 (Mt. 22:37)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (3)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can glorify God above all else. A person can glorify God by obeying God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Word just as it is given, no matter the cost (Ge. 22:2, 10).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he that doeth the will of my Father which is in heaven\u8221\'94 (Mt. 7:21)\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge22.1-2&off=0&ctx=startling+passage.)%0a~1+(22:1%E2%80%932)+Testing%E2%80%94S"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 134\endash 135). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (4)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can reach an unusual height of spiritual maturity, a maturity that stands out as a great testimony for God (Ge. 22:2, 5, 7\endash 8, 10\endash 11, 13\endash 14).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven\u8221\'94 (Mt. 5:16)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Be ye therefore perfect, even as your Father which is in heaven is perfect\u8221\'94 (Mt. 5:48)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And he said to [them] all, If any [man] will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me\u8221\'94 (Lu. 9:23)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But ye shall receive power, after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you: and ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judaea, and in Samaria, and unto the uttermost part of the earth\u8221\'94 (Ac. 1:8)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And he said, The God of our fathers hath chosen thee, that thou shouldest know his will, and see that Just One, and shouldest hear the voice of his mouth. For thou shalt be his witness unto all men of what thou hast seen and heard\u8221\'94 (Ac. 22:14\endash 15)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ye are my witnesses, saith the }{\f0\fs24\b1\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24\b1 , and my servant whom I have chosen: that ye may know and believe me, and understand that I am he: before me there was no God formed, neither shall there be after me\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 (Is. 43:10)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (5)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can be completely surrendered to God. A person can give back to God the greatest gift of all, the very gift that God had given the person in the first place, his body and his life (Ge. 22:1\endash 2, 9\endash 10). A person can make the absolute sacrifice of himself to God (Ge. 22:1f).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge22.1-2&off=6211&ctx=rams%E2%80%9D+(1+S.+15:22).%0a~(4)+Abraham+demonstr"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 135). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (6)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s faith can be victorious over all, no matter the trial (Ge. 22:1f).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now thanks be unto God, which always causeth us to triumph in Christ, and maketh manifest the savour of his knowledge by us in every place\u8221\'94 (2 Co. 2:14).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93For whatsoever is born of God overcometh the world: and this is the victory that overcometh the world, even our faith. Who is he that overcometh the world, but he that believeth that Jesus is the Son of God?\u8221\'94 (1 Jn. 5:4\endash 5).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (7)\tab Abraham demonstrated that a person can put God first, before all else, no matter the cost (Ge. 22:1\endash 2, 9\endash 10).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge22.1-2&off=8170&ctx=s%E2%80%9D+(1+Co.+6:19%E2%80%9320).%0a~(6)+Abraham+demonstr"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 135). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
